Description:
SPACE, COMFORT AND COLLINGWOOD HISTORY
This wide block-fronted residence, built in 1917, is next door to the birthplace of the legendary John Wren, whose first betting business was centred around Gold Street and the adjacent laneways. A wide hallway opens from the front verandah to three exceptionally spacious and well-lit bedrooms. Double doors lead to the well-proportioned living and dining room, open to a modern kitchen with polished concrete floors. To one side is a good-sized bathroom, with free standing clawfoot bath and separate shower, and a laundry recess. Timber and glass folding doors open to a pergola and bluestone paved courtyard to two sides. Featuring timber floorboards and reverse-cycle air conditioning, here is a sunny family home providing comfortable living for many years to come, with potential to add further value in a rapidly appreciating precinct close to cafes, transport and freeway access.
Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
EDWARDIAN APPEAL, CITY-EDGE ATTRACTION – SIMPLY IRRESISTIBLE!
Complete with dual-street frontage and tasteful enhancements throughout, this impeccable period home delivers an enticing lifestyle of space, quality and unmatched convenience. Behind its elegant façade, the home’s rejuvenated interior features two large bedrooms and updated semi-ensuite bathroom, contemporary kitchen with all-Bosch appliances, big living/dining area. Other highlights include gas heating and ducted evaporative cooling, attic ladder to expansive in-roof storage, big laundry and separate toilet, plus double doors out to a fabulous north-facing entertainers’ courtyard as well as off-street parking via Little Wellington Street. Walk to Smith Street cafés and shops, trams to the CBD – a terrific opportunity to reside or invest in a prime city-edge location.

Description:
Penthouse Perfect, Plus Potential!
Sweeping views to the distant ranges from a bank of huge windows creates a spectacular backdrop to this stylish top floor warehouse apartment in the exciting Foy & Gibson lifestyle precinct. A stunning designer fit-out under soaring 4m ceilings is brilliantly enhanced by hydronic heating and air-conditioning delivering sublime penthouse living. Including lift access, basement parking and storage cage; this single-storey apartment also presents the last chance in the building to add a second level/spectacular roof deck when ready. This opportunity may never be offered again! Comprises two double bedrooms (walk-in-robe, built-in-robe), open-plan living and dining with HeatnGlo fireplace, excellent kitchen with European appliances, stone-finished bathroom, European laundry and secure intercom entry. Step out to cafes, shopping, galleries and city trams.

Description:
So Cool...
Let's begin with the drive through Melbourne's most creative street, a feeling that you're in New York with a mix of cool warehouse conversions, then the location, just around the corner to Melbourne's most cool and convenient streets Smith or Gertrude and the apartment that follows the trends outside from the building entrance to inside its light filled interior that is just so cool.
You will be impressed upon entering a entrance hallway that proceeds you through a hard to beat floorplan that offers: A totally private bedroom, stylish separate bathroom with hidden laundry and open plan living with easy to like kitchen and polished concrete floors that opens out onto a really cool private terrace that allows you to entertain in style.
Adding to your excitement are some inner city living essentials that include secure basement car park, bike racks and storage cage.
Now 21 Is Your New Key To Become Cool...

Description:
Executor's Auction
This contemporary two storey freestanding townhouse on a wider than normal allotment may abut Hoddle Street at the rear but at an entry level price you'll get a lot of house for a reasonable price. There's two bedrooms with robes upstairs where the main with a bit of work could possibly be made in to two rooms and an open plan living area with meals adjoining kitchen.
Ample glass doors and windows abound to allow natural light to stream through the home and provide a vista across the front and rear paved yards. Presented in a very comfortable and honest manner this property will enable you to move in or lease today whilst considering improvements for the future.
We're sure you'll see that the attributes of this home outweigh the minor inconvenience of being adjacent Hoddle Street

Description:
A Matter of Style & Security!
Take the best elements of easy inner-city living and place them in a central and convenient position for a lifestyle of pure pleasure with this stylish and secure contemporary apartment boasting two levels and stunning city views. Quality tenants and good returns (February, 2012) complement a brilliant investment or occupier opportunity offering rich rewards in a highly-coveted corner complex where this immaculate 'as-new' home features basement car space, storage cage and video intercom entry. Walk to superb cafes, exciting shopping, trams, train station and the Fitzroy Pool and enjoy entrance foyer, two double bedrooms with built-robes, two fabulous bathrooms, excellent open-plan living/dining area flowing to entertainment terrace with city outlook, gourmet stone kitchen with stainless-steel appliances, European laundry, split-system heating/cooling and polished hardwood floors.
Belinda Lindsay : 0409 853 769

Description:
Lifestyle Central…
Reflecting Collingwood’s old world charm amidst a diverse streetscape of period homes, converted warehouses and small commercial premises is this delightful semi-detached Victorian terrace offered in beautiful order with a flexible floor plan that could accommodate up to 3 bedrooms. With a harmonious blend of period detail and modern amenity the home is sure to charm and enjoys a location walking distance to the diverse cafes of Smith and Brunswick Streets, the CBD, a host of public transport options and the hallowed turf of the MCG.
With a sun drenched rear Northerly aspect and handsome block fronted facade this spacious home features 2 large bedrooms, flexible 3rd bedroom/additional living/dining with bi-fold doors, formal lounge, renovated bathroom with laundry facilities, updated kitchen/meals with dishwasher and a delightfully rustic outdoor area with feature decking, cabinetry, corrugated water tank and sustainable veggie patches...Whilst we’re thinking ‘sustainability’ the home also offers solar HWS and an additional water tank plumbed to the toilet.
Insights: 90 Sackville Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2020 and 24 other 3 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.
